import React from 'react';
import { Container, Typography, List, ListItem, ListItemText, Divider, LinearProgress, CircularProgress } from '@mui/material';
import {
  EmojiObjects as EmojiObjectsIcon,
  SentimentVerySatisfied as SentimentVerySatisfiedIcon,
  Code as CodeIcon,
  People as PeopleIcon,
  ThumbUp as ThumbUpIcon,
  QuestionAnswer as QuestionAnswerIcon,
  FormatListNumbered as FormatListNumberedIcon,
  Spellcheck as SpellcheckIcon,
  ChatBubbleOutline as ChatBubbleOutlineIcon,
} from '@mui/icons-material';


const MethodologyContent = () => {
  return (
    <>
      <Typography variant="h4" gutterBottom>
        Methodology
      </Typography>

      <Typography variant="h6" style={{ marginTop: '1.5rem' }}>
        Quantitative Insights
      </Typography>

      <Typography>
        The survey conducted among educators yielded valuable quantitative data, offering insights into their perspectives on various educational practices and initiatives. Key quantitative findings include:
      </Typography>

      <List>
        <ListItem>
          <ListItemIcon>
            <ArrowRightIcon color="primary" />
          </ListItemIcon>
          <ListItemText primary="Multimedia Integration: 80% of educators agreed or strongly agreed that including multimedia enriches cognitive engagement in learning." />
        </ListItem>
        <ListItem>
          <ListItemIcon>
            <ArrowRightIcon color="primary" />
          </ListItemIcon>
          <ListItemText primary="Emotional Impact: 80% of educators consider the dynamic influence of instructional media on students' learning adventures." />
        </ListItem>
        <ListItem>
          <ListItemIcon>
            <ArrowRightIcon color="primary" />
          </ListItemIcon>
          <ListItemText primary="Technology-Enabled Simulations: 60% of educators agreed that integrating technology-enabled simulations enhances critical thinking and problem-solving abilities." />
        </ListItem>
        <ListItem>
          <ListItemIcon>
            <ArrowRightIcon color="primary" />
          </ListItemIcon>
          <ListItemText primary="Least Restrictive Environment (LRE) Initiative: 60% were neutral, while 40% strongly agreed with promoting a more inclusive and equitable learning environment." />
        </ListItem>
        <ListItem>
          <ListItemIcon>
            <ArrowRightIcon color="primary" />
          </ListItemIcon>
          <ListItemText primary="Common Core State Standards (CCSS) and Universal Design for Learning (UDL): 60% indicated agreement with the effectiveness of CCSS, while 40% expressed a neutral stance regarding UDL's contribution to a more thorough learning experience." />
        </ListItem>
      </List>

      <Typography variant="h6" style={{ marginTop: '1.5rem' }}>
        Qualitative Insights
      </Typography>

      <Typography>
        Analyzing open-ended responses from educators, qualitative insights emerged, emphasizing the need for:
      </Typography>

      <List>
        <ListItem>
          <ListItemIcon>
            <ArrowRightIcon color="primary" />
          </ListItemIcon>
          <ListItemText primary="Formative Assessments: We are incorporating formative assessments to monitor student progress." />
        </ListItem>
        <ListItem>
          <ListItemIcon>
            <ArrowRightIcon color="primary" />
          </ListItemIcon>
          <ListItemText primary="Criterion-Referenced Elements: They integrate criterion-referenced elements, such as defined learning objectives and rubrics, to ensure alignment with educational standards." />
        </ListItem>
        <ListItem>
          <ListItemIcon>
            <ArrowRightIcon color="primary" />
          </ListItemIcon>
          <ListItemText primary="Collaborative Environment: They are creating a collaborative environment for educators to share best practices and strategies, fostering a comprehensive approach to curricular design." />
        </ListItem>
        <ListItem>
          <ListItemIcon>
            <ArrowRightIcon color="primary" />
          </ListItemIcon>
          <ListItemText primary="Ethnographic Interviewing: We incorporate ethnographic interviewing to better understand educators' perspectives by considering cultural, social, and contextual factors." />
        </ListItem>
      </List>

      <Typography>
        Overall, this combined quantitative and qualitative approach provides a nuanced understanding of educators' viewpoints and suggests areas for improvement within educational practices and initiatives.
      </Typography>
    </>
  );
};

export default MethodologyContent;
